  "title": "Senior Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Prepares cost estimates as required.</p><p>- Preparation of measurement sheets and assists in quantity take-off as required.</p><p>- Assist in estimation of direct & indirect costs for sub-contract sublet.</p><p>- Monitors and records site progress and keep records of day works.</p><p>- Checks the allocation of manpower and productivity. Prepares comparison sheets for quotations from suppliers and subcontractors.</p><p>- Preparation of payments advice and review then certify claim submission for subcontractors and suppliers.</p><p>- Assist in claims preparation in coordination with the Project Manager/Director.</p><p>- Follow up payments from main contractor/consultant/client.</p><p>- Assist the PD/PM to establish and operate project cost control.</p><p>- Provides advice on contractual claims, VO or other contractual matters.</p><p>- Measures and computes values to variations and prepares interim and/or final accounts.</p><p>- To provide estimate, computations & work on contractual/technical/project change orders.</p><p>- Prepares monthly progress payments to main contractors/consultant/clients.</p><p></p><p>REQUIREMENTS / QUALIFICATIONS</p><p>- Degree or Diploma in Building, Quantity Surveying or equivalent</p><p>- Computer literate, Microsoft office</p><p>- Excellent oral and written communication skills with proficiency in English</p><p>- With construction background</p><p>- Min 3 years relevant work experience</p><p>- Possess good mathematical and accounting skills</p><p>- Able to work independently and in teams</p><p>- Plays an active role with great initiatives in the project execution to complete the task on time with the optimum utilization of resources.</p>",
